jokes.title: Math Teacher: If I have 5 bottles in one hand and 6 in the other hand, what do I have?
jokes.body: Student: A drinking problem

jokes.title: I was up all night looking for the sun
jokes.body: Then it dawned on me

jokes.title: Today, while constipated, I decided to solve a difficult math problem.
jokes.body: I was able to work it out with my pencil.

jokes.title: I just wrote a review of a book that argues that math charts should use bolder lines.
jokes.body: My review: "The plot thickens"

jokes.title: There's no new jokes about math
jokes.body: It's all derivatives

jokes.title: The one who created the memes font really changed the world.
jokes.body: I mean, he really made an impact.

jokes.title: I received a letter from my opticians, but I'm concerned about their print.
jokes.body: Either it's failing or they used a blurry font. So weird.

jokes.title: I saw a giant mouse so I tried killing it with a baseball bat.
jokes.body: So now I have a lifetime ban from Disneyland.

jokes.title: I put some batteries in my mouse yesterday.
jokes.body: And now I'm banned from the pet store.

jokes.title: Patient: "Doctor, doctor! I broke my arm in two places."
jokes.body: Doctor: "Then don't go to those places."

jokes.title: Macbeth.docx
jokes.body: That's a play on word.

jokes.title: If you serve your kids frozen pizza or chicken nuggests for tea, you are a terrible parent.
jokes.body: I don't care how busy you are, at least find the time to microwave them first.

jokes.title: What came first, the chicken or the egg?
jokes.body: An egg can't come.

jokes.title: Did you know that humans eat more bananas than monkeys?
jokes.body: When was the last time you ate a monkey?

jokes.title: "I'm going bananas."
jokes.body: That's what I tell the bananas when I'm leaving the house.

jokes.title: I'm starting a minimalist orchestra!
jokes.body: It's just like a regular orchestra but without the bells and whistles.

jokes.title: My friend has designed an invisible aeroplane.
jokes.body: I can't see it taking off.

jokes.title: I really don't like thinking about gravity.
jokes.body: It always brings me down.

jokes.title: Did you hear about the activist who fought agains gravity?
jokes.body: They started an uprising.

jokes.title: Everything was great until gravity was invented.
jokes.body: Things went downhill after that.

jokes.title: Gravity is really important as a fundamental force of nature.
jokes.body: But if you get rid of it you get gravy.

jokes.title: I'm reading a book about anti-gravity.
jokes.body: It's a nice bit of light reading.

jokes.title: What's the most terrifying word in experimental nuclear physics?
jokes.body: Oops!

jokes.title: I will name my son Physics.
jokes.body: So that I will be called the Father of Physics.

jokes.title: A bunch of neutrinos walk through a bar.
A teacher asks Little Jonny, "What do you want to be when you grow up?"
jokes.body:
Little Jonny replies, "I want to be a policeman and follow my dad's footsteps."

"But your dad isn't a policeman Jonny."

"I know, he's a burglar."

jokes.title: My balloon elephant wouldn't fit in the back seat of my car.
jokes.body: So I had to pop the trunk.

jokes.title: A man has been stealing wheels of police cars.
jokes.body: Police are working tirelessly to catch him.

jokes.title: What's worse than finding a bomb under your car?
jokes.body: Not finding it.

jokes.title: Almost every day I hear car alarms going off around the city.
jokes.body: But never in my life have I seen a car wake up.

jokes.title: The cop asked, "Whose car is this? Where are you headed? What do you do?"
jokes.body: The miner replied, "Mine."

jokes.title: A man is driving home from work when he gets a call from his wife.
jokes.body:
"Be careful on the road honey. I heard on the news that there's a car going the wrong way on the highway."

"It's not just one car," he responds, "It's hundreds of them!"

jokes.title: My car mechanic called me and said, "You can pick up your car by 5 PM."
jokes.body: I said, "I don't think I'll be strong enough by then."

jokes.title: Two men are working on a car.
jokes.body:
One man says, "Let's call it a day."

The other man says, "Well, that's a weird name for a car."

jokes.title: What do you call a belt made out of watches?
jokes.body: A waist of time.

jokes.title: Why do the ferris wheel and the merry-go-round never go on holiday together?
jokes.body: Because they travel on different planes.

jokes.title: I told my kinds I was gonna take them to that place with the ferris wheel and cotton candy, but instead I took them to the dentist.
jokes.body: They said it wasn't fair.

jokes.title: My girlfriend broke up with me at our favourite date spot. I was so shocked and heart-broken I got up and immediately stormed out the door.
jokes.body: And that's how I fell off the ferris wheel.

jokes.title: Calculus has a steep learning curve.
jokes.body: But at least you know exactly how steep the learning curve is!

jokes.title: Someone told me they didn't like calculus.
jokes.body: I told them their opinion would change over time.

jokes.title: I failed my calculus exam because I was sitting between two identical twins.
jokes.body: It was impossible to differentiate between them.

jokes.title: I can tolerate algebra, maybe even a little calculus.
jokes.body: But geometry is where I draw the line.

jokes.title: I failed calculus when we reached differentiation.
jokes.body: I guess I should have known my limits. I could barely derive anything from what the teacher taught us.

jokes.title: There are many problems with math puns.
jokes.body: Calculus jokes are mostly derivative, trigonometry jokes are too graphic, algebra jokes are usually formulaic, and arithmetic jokes are pretty basic. But the occasional statistics joke is an outlier.

jokes.title: My friend said that I make people uncomfortable by invading their personal space.
jokes.body: It was a very hurtful thing to say and it completely ruined our bath.

jokes.title: My friend told me his dog could bring him a ball from a mile away.
jokes.body: Sounds pretty far fetched.

jokes.title: I called my wife and told her that I'll pick up pizza and coke on the way back from work. But is seems she was not happy.
jokes.body: She still regrets letting me name the kids.

jokes.title: An apple a day keeps the doctor away.
jokes.body: Especially if you throw it at him.

jokes.title: How did the hackers get away from the crime scene?
jokes.body: They ransomware.

jokes.title: My computer program won't run.
jokes.body: Do I need to install legs or something?

jokes.title: How did computers run before Microsoft?
jokes.body: Well.

jokes.title: Me: Sorry I'm late. I was having computer issues.
jokes.body:
Boss: Hard drive?

Me: The commute was fine. It's my laptop.

jokes.title: I've just bought one of those new singing computers.
jokes.body: It's a Dell.

jokes.title: My password is "Incorrect".
jokes.body: That way, if I type in a different password, it reminds me "Your password is incorrect". And then I remember.

jokes.title: Why is the computer keyboard working so hard?
jokes.body: Because it has two shifts.

jokes.title: My doctor told me the only exercise that will get rid of my big belly.
jokes.body: I asked him if I should join a gym. He said, "No, that's not necessary. Here's the exercise you need: move your head back and forth from left to right anytime someone asks you if you'd like something to eat."

jokes.title: My New Year's Resolution is to exercise more.
jokes.body: I hope it works out.

jokes.title: How many mathematicians does it take to change a lightbulb?
jokes.body: The punchline is trivial and has been left as an exercise for the reader.

jokes.title: Doctor: How often do you exercise?
jokes.body:
Me: 3 times.

Doctor: A week? A month?

Me: I have given my answer.

jokes.title: My dad died because of a lack of exercise.
jokes.body: He didn't run when the bus was coming.

jokes.title: I don't exercise when I'm sick.
jokes.body: My nose does the running for me.

jokes.title: Exercise is like a drug to me.
jokes.body: That's why I'm drug free.

jokes.title: I never thought I'd be the type of person to wake up at 5 in the morning to exercise.
jokes.body: I was right.

jokes.title: I respect giraffes.
jokes.body: They're an animal I can look up to.

jokes.title: Why didn't the audience laugh at the giraffe's joke?
jokes.body: It went over their heads.

jokes.title: A giraffe can grow up to 18 feet.
jokes.body: But they usually only have 4.

jokes.title: Why is it cheap to feed a giraffe?
jokes.body: A little goes a long way.

jokes.title: A giraffe walks into a bar.
jokes.body: Giraffes aren't good at playing limbo.

jokes.title: 500 bricks on a plane
jokes.body:
There are 500 bricks on a plane, one falls off, how many are left?

499

What are the 3 simple steps of putting an elephant in a refrigerator?

Open refrigerator, put elephant in, close refrigerator.

What are the 4 simple steps of putting a giraffe in a refrigerator?

Open refrigerator, take elephant out, put giraffe in, close refigerator.

It's the lion's birthday and he invites everyone in the jungle. Everyone turns up but one animal, which animal is it and why?

The giraffe, he's in the refrigerator.

Sally is an explorer. She is walking through a jungle when suddenly she comes across a crocodile infested river. There are no bridges over it. Sally swims over and is not bitten by a single crocodile. How?

All the crocodiles are at the lion's party.

Sally dies anyway, why?

She is hit in the head by a brick.

jokes.title: I caught a bus yesterday.
jokes.body: Now I need to buy a new fishing rod.

jokes.title: What do you get if you cross a river with a school bus?
jokes.body: Fired.

jokes.title: I heard a joke about a speeding bus the other day.
jokes.body: I didn't get it at first. Then it hit me.

jokes.title: Don't want to die alone?
jokes.body: Become a bus driver.

jokes.title: Not saying I live in a rough area, but I just bought an advent calendar and half the windows are boarded up.
The CEO of IKEA was elected Prime Minister in Sweden.
jokes.body: He should have his cabinet together by the end of the weekend.

jokes.title: Before I criticise a man, I like to walk a mile in his shoes.
jokes.body: That way, when I do criticise him, I'm a mile away and I have his shoes.

jokes.title: I'm great at multitasking. I can waste time, be unproductive, and procrastinate all at once.
Today a man knocked on my door and asked for a small donation towards the local swimming pool.
jokes.body: I gave him a glass of water.

jokes.title: I think my neightbour is stalking me as she's been googling my name on her computer.
jokes.body: I saw it through my telescope last night.

jokes.title: Intelligence is like underwear.
jokes.body: It's important that you have it, but not necessary that you show it off.

jokes.title: Apparently I snore so loudly that it scares everyone in the car I'm driving.
I can't believe I got fired from the calendar factory.
jokes.body: All I did was take a day off.

jokes.title: I tried to explain to my 4-year-old son that's perfectly normal to accidentally poop your pants, but he's still making fun of me.
Lance is an uncommon name nowadays.
jokes.body: But in medieval times people were named Lanced a lot.

jokes.title: My wife and I were happy for twenty years.
jokes.body: Then we met.

jokes.title: I used to think I was undecisive, but now I'm not too sure.
I have a few jokes about unemployed people.
jokes.body: Unfortunately none of them work.

jokes.title: That awkward moment when you leave a store without buying anything.
jokes.body: All you can think is, "Act natural, you're innocent."

jokes.title: The problem with trouble shooting is that trouble shoots back.
Did you hear about the guy who got hit in the head with a can of soda?
jokes.body: He was lucky it was a soft drink.

jokes.title: I want to die peacefully in my sleep like my grandfather.
jokes.body: Not screaming and yelling like the passengers in his car.

jokes.title: I'd tell you a chemistry joke, but I know I wouldn't get a reaction.
I'm glad I know sign language.
jokes.body: It's pretty handy.

jokes.title: I asked my wife to embrace her mistakes.
jokes.body: She gave me a hug.

jokes.title: ebay is so useless.
jokes.body: I tried looking up lighters and all they had was 13,749 matches.

jokes.title: Don't trust atoms.
jokes.body: They make up everything.

jokes.title: Don't spell part backwards.
jokes.body: It's a trap.

jokes.title: The future, the present and the past walked into a bar.
jokes.body: Things got a little tense.

jokes.title: I became addicted to the hokey pokey.
jokes.body: Thankfully I turned myself around.

jokes.title: Thanks for explaining the word "many" to me.
jokes.body: It means a lot.

jokes.title: Just read that 4,153,237 people got married last year.
jokes.body: Not to cause any trouble, but shouldn't that be an even number?

jokes.title: Life is all about perspective.
jokes.body: The sinking of the Titanic was a miracle to the lobsters in the ship's kitchen.

jokes.title: Feeling pretty proud of myself.
jokes.body: The Sesame Street puzzle I bought said 3 - 5 years, but I finished it in 18 months.

jokes.title: I gave up my seat to a blind person in the bus.
jokes.body: That is how I lost my job as a bus driver.

jokes.title: Just burned 2,000 calories.
jokes.body: That's the last time I leave brownies in the oven while I nap.

jokes.title: I married my wife for her looks.
jokes.body: But not the ones she's giving me lately.

jokes.title: I'm not saying your perfume is too strong.
jokes.body: I'm just saying the canary was alive before you got here.

jokes.title: The police just knocked on my door and told me that my dogs were chasing people on bikes.
jokes.body: My dogs don't even own bikes.

jokes.title: I can totally keep secrets.
jokes.body: It's the people I tell them to that can't.

jokes.title: The universe is made up of protons, neutrons, electrons and morons.
I bought a vacuum cleaner six months ago.
jokes.body: So far all it's been doing is gathering dust.

jokes.title: My girlfriend said, "You act like a detective too much. I want to split up."
jokes.body: "Good idea," I replied. "We can cover more ground that way."

jokes.title: If you think nobody cares wheter you're alive, try missing a couple payments.
I'd tell you a joke about poo, but it would stink.
A German shepherd poos on my lawn every day.
jokes.body: Yesterday he brought a dog.

jokes.title: Putin is reportedly extremely angry about his bridge getting blown up.
jokes.body: He needs to get over it.

jokes.title: What do you call Postman Pat after he retires?
jokes.body: Pat.

jokes.title: As a doctor I often get asked why I use that rubber hammer to tap patient's knees.
jokes.body: I don't know. I just get a kick out of it.

jokes.title: Doctor, doctor! I can't feel my legs!
jokes.body: "I know," says the doctor, "I amputated your arms."

jokes.title: Me: "Doctor, doctor! I feel like a deck of cards."
jokes.body: Doctor: "Sit down, I'll deal with you later."

jokes.title: "Doctor doctor! there's a man on the phone who claims he's invisible!"
jokes.body: Doctor: "Well tell him I can't see him right now."

jokes.title: Patient: "Doctor, doctor! I see double!"
jokes.body:
Doctor: "Sit on the chair please."

Patient: "Which one?"

jokes.title: Patient: "Doctor, doctor! I only have 59 seconds to live!"
jokes.body: Doctor: "Hang on a minute."

jokes.title: A guy isn't feeling well, and goes to the doctor.
jokes.body:
Doctor: "I have good news and bad news. Which do you want first?"

The guy: "I guess I'll get the good news first."

Doctor: "You're going to get something named after you."

jokes.title: My doctor told me that I was going deaf 3 years ago.
jokes.body: I haven't heard from him since.

jokes.title: Doctor: "You don't look too good. Do you smoke or drink alcohol?"
jokes.body: Me: "I drink it."

jokes.title: Patient: "Doctor, doctor! Every time I drink coffee I get pain in my eye."
jokes.body: Doctor: "Take the spoon out of your cup."

jokes.title: Doctor (handing me my new born baby): "I'm sorry but your wife didn't make it."
jokes.body: Me (handing the baby back to him): "Bring me the one my wife made."

jokes.title: My doctor gave me three months to live.
jokes.body: When I told him I wouldn't be able to come up with the money to pay the bill by then, he gave me three more.

jokes.title: Patient: "Doctor, doctor! I'm addicted to Twitter!"
jokes.body: Doctor: "Sorry, I don't follow you."

jokes.title: Doctor: "I have good news and bad news."
jokes.body:
Patient: "What's the good news?"

Doctor: "The good news is you have 24 hours left to live."

Patient: "What's the bad new?"

Doctor: "The bad news is I should've told you that yesterday."

jokes.title: Doctor: "Well, your arm is broken. You'll need a cast for about 8 weeks and you'll be good as new."
jokes.body:
Me: "When the cast comes off, will I be able to play the piano?"

Doctor: "I don't see why not."

Me: "Awesome! I've always wanted to play the piano."

jokes.title: The doctor gave me these pills and said I need to take one pill everyday for the rest of my life.
jokes.body: I looked at the bottle and said, "But doctor, there are only 3 pills in here."

jokes.title: My husband and I role played in bed last night for 3 hours. He was the doctor and I was the patient.
jokes.body: I was in the waiting room for 2 hours and 58 minutes.

jokes.title: I was charged $200 just to see a doctor.
jokes.body: And I don't even get to keep the binoculars.

jokes.title: Patient: "Doctor, doctor! I'm having dark thoughts and I may be suicidal. What should I do?"
jokes.body: Doctor: "Pay in advance."

jokes.title: I lost three fingers on my right hand, so I asked my doctor if I would still be able to write with it.
jokes.body: He said: "Maybe, but I wouldn't count on it.

jokes.title: As a doctor, I never make a joke about vaccines.
jokes.body: But I think I'll give it a shot.

jokes.title: I told my doctor I have one coffee every day.
jokes.body: Eight cups, but it's the same coffee.
